args: Do you train that hard every day?
It's the only way I'll get stronger.
...It seems I owe you an apology.
The more I watch you, the more I come\nto see you for who you really are.
You are an honest, hardworking,\nand beloved man.
I'm sorry I ever doubted your integrity.
Well, don't worry about it. It's not like your\ndoubting me did any lasting harm.
But the whole reason you came here was\nto watch over me, right?
If you don't need to do so anymore,\ndoes that mean you're going to leave?
Whatcha doin', Reverend? ...Oooo!\nAre you on a daaaate?!
Silence! I will hear no more of this\nfoolishness!
Ha ha ha! You're in trouuuble!
What was that about you being their\nteacher?
Wherever there is a shortage of teachers,\npreachers must step in to help the children\nwith their studies.
Do you have a problem with that?!
Not at all. I think it suits you.
W-well... Anyway, back to what we were\ndiscussing...
Calm down, children. I'm not going\nanywhere.
Are you sure you want to stay, Estelle?
Leaving now would be tantamount to\nabandoning these children.
A preacher cannot be so irresponsible.
The children aren't the only ones who\nwould be sad if you left, you know?\nI would be, too.
Revereeeeend! Your face is soooo red!
Estelle and {player_name},\nsittin' in a tree! K-I-S—
This calls for the Loving Hand!
